track_notes: Short and steep off-trail hike (0.5 miles/460EG) at the end of a long and rough FS road (~11 miles).  FS Road is open seasonally 3/18 - 12/20 and you will need a high-clearance 4WD to drive all the way to the parking spot.  I recommend driving this route only in dry conditions and if you are okay with some pinstriping.  This route avoids the large private property inholding (which is posted) on the north side of the ridge and is entirely within the National Forest.

Turn on FS 190 off of Bumpus Cove Road (36.16068, -82.47863).  The first 7.4 miles of FS 190 is rocky and bumpy but is pretty standard for a TN FS road.  In the middle of a hairpin turn (36.12386, -82.48415) FS 190 turns right and goes up the ridge line.  The road changes character at this point and becomes a tighter and rougher two track lane.  Numerous small ruts and mudholes but they all had solid bottoms in very dry conditions.  Around mile 9.3 (36.11437, -82.51140) you will enter a clearing with a campsite on the left.  Beyond this clearing the road gets rougher for the last mile and 4WD will likely be needed.  If in doubt, park here and walk the last mile.
